
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `amixer` baraye tanzim va kontrole sedaye karthaye sound (sound cards) dar Linux estefade mishavad.  Ba `amixer` shoma mitavanid volume-ha ra tagheer dahid, seda ra mute ya unmute konid, va gozinehaye mokhtalefe karthaye sound ra tanzim konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `amixer sget Master` --> 🔊 Gereftan volume-haye asly.
    🔹 `amixer sset Master 50%` --> 🎧 Tagheer dadan volume asli be 50 darsad.
    🔹 `amixer sset Master mute` --> 🔇 Mute kardane sedaye asli.
    🔹 `amixer sset Master unmute` --> 🔈 Unmute kardane sedaye asli.
    🔹 `amixer controls` --> 🎛️ List kardane hameye control-haye mojood baraye kart-e seda.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ amixer sget Master

    🔹 Namayesh volume-haye asli.

    $ amixer sset Master 75%+

    🔹 Afzayesh volume asli be andazeye 75 darsad az volume-haye konooni.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ amixer sset Master 20%-

    🔹 Kam kardane volume-haye asli be andazeye 20 darsad az volume-haye konooni. Agar volume 30 darsad bood, hala 10 darsad mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `amixer` command is used for managing and controlling sound card settings in Linux.  With `amixer`, you can change volumes, mute or unmute sound, and configure various options for your sound cards.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `amixer sget Master` --> 🔊 Get the current master volume levels.
    🔹 `amixer sset Master 50%` --> 🎧 Set the master volume to 50%.
    🔹 `amixer sset Master mute` --> 🔇 Mute the master volume.
    🔹 `amixer sset Master unmute` --> 🔈 Unmute the master volume.
    🔹 `amixer controls` --> 🎛️ List all available controls for the sound card.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ amixer sget Master

    🔹 Display the current master volume settings.

    $ amixer sset Master 75%+

    🔹 Increase the master volume by 75% relative to the current volume.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ amixer sset Master 20%-

    🔹 Decrease the master volume by 20% relative to the current volume. If the volume was at 30%, it will now be at 10%.

